properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 3 at 2:45PM PST until February 5 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulation of 8 to 16 inches
Tuesday night and Wednesday morning.

* WHERE...Cascade mountains including the Mount Baker Ski Area,
Stevens Pass, and Snoqualmie Pass, the Crystal Mountain Ski
Area, and Paradise on Mount Rainier.

* WHEN...From 4 PM Tuesday to 10 AM PST Wednesday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult Tuesday night and
Wednesday morning before the snow level rises above the passes.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The snow level will rise from below 1000
feet Tuesday morning to around 4000 feet Wednesday morning and
will further rise to around 5500 feet in the southern Cascades
Wednesday night and Thursday.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

For the latest road conditions in Washington state, call 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM TUESDAY TO 10 AM PST WEDNESDAY
